HEADWORD: Pitted
<hw>Pit"ted</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧t"t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Marked with little pits, as in smallpox. See <er>Pit</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having minute thin spots; <as>as,
<ex>pitted</ex> ducts in the vascular parts of vegetable
tissue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitter</ent>⟦br⟧
